# GLOBAL RULES
1. No use of type `any`
2. No Vietnamese messages inside code
3. All texts must be defined in shared constants files
4. No comments in code
5. No random or unnecessary line breaks
6. Full strict typing across all layers
7. Each feature must be fully completed before starting another
8. All API contracts must be consistent and strongly typed
9. Use camelCase for all variables, functions, and file naming (except database columns)
10. Enforce complete Global Rules across the project
11. ESLint must always be enabled and enforced
12. All unused code must be removed immediately (variables, imports, functions, components)
13. Always follow clean code principles; code must be clear, readable, and maintainable
14. Always optimize imports; avoid deep or redundant import paths
15. Enforce clear separation of concerns: UI, business logic, data access, validations, and utilities must not mix
16. Avoid duplication of logic across modules; extract reusable utilities when needed
17. Use pure functions whenever possible to ensure predictable behavior
18. Centralize all configuration; no inline configuration or magic values allowed
19. Validate environment variables before application startup
20. Enforce consistent naming conventions across all modules
21. Prevent deep nesting; use early returns and refactoring
22. All system messages must be stored in centralized message constants
23. All input fields must enforce maximum length validation
24. All fields must be validated using correct format (email, phone, uuid, numeric, date, etc.)
25. Please remove code declared but its value is never read
26. Always fix format problems by Prettier